11/10/07
set up from NewProtex 3.0.1

goal: 
make a gui-free application for protein folding
	for game and evolution
	

five modes:

<aaseq> = single-letter aa seq
<aa radius> = radius of aa to use when rendering
<target shape string> = list of directions for folding target shape
<filename.gif/png> = filename with extension specifying type

PALETTE:
server -p <aa radius> <filename.gif/png>
		

TARGET:
server -t <aa radius> <target shape string> <filename.gif/png>
		saves gif/png of target shape in same dir as app

PICTURE:
server -p <aa radius> <aaseq> <filename.gif/png>
	ssBonds OFF
	saves gif/png of folded protein in same dir as app
	returns color

server -P <aaseq> <filename>
	ssBonds ON
	saves gif/png of folded protein in same dir as app
	returns color

COLOR:
server -c <aaseq>
	ssBonds OFF
	returns color

server -C <aaseq>
	ssBonds ON
	returns color
	
MATCH:
server -m <aa radius> <aaseq> <target shape string> <filename.gif/png>
	ssBonds OFF
	saves gif/png of folded protein in same dir as app
	returns true/false for match
	
server -M <aa radius> <aaseq> <target shape string> <filename.gif/png>
	ssBonds ON
	saves gif/png of folded protein in same dir as app
	returns true/false for match
	

PLAN:
1) bring it down to just aapalette & one folding window
2) pull out AApainter as static method object for drawing aas
	differnt drawBigAA; drawTinyAA methods
3) test to develop tiny aas
4) get it to make .gif & .png
